<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-28T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="748" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/47<hi rend="superscript">4/22</hi>: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-28T12:00:00-04:00">June
                                        28, 1940—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your June 28, 10 a.m., and June 27, 7 p.m. The American Government
                                definitely purchased this wolfram and antimony and shipments are to
                                be consigned to an agency of the American Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>